                            <comment id="17863392" author="beobal" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2024 17:31:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is with sharing the same start time (&lt;tt&gt;RequestTime.startedAtNanos()&lt;/tt&gt;) for the timing of each individual read query, which was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19534&quot; title=&quot;Unbounded queues in native transport requests lead to node instability&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19534&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19534&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
This results in accumulation so that the latency reported for query &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; includes the latency of &lt;em&gt;(n-1)&lt;/em&gt; + &lt;em&gt;(n-2)&lt;/em&gt; + &lt;em&gt;(n-3)&lt;/em&gt; etc.&lt;br/&gt;
The fix is trivial and doesn&apos;t affect the other aspects of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19534&quot; title=&quot;Unbounded queues in native transport requests lead to node instability&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19534&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19534&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;4.1 patch:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3404&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3404&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;5.0 patch:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3405&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3405&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;trunk patch:&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3406&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/3406&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There are 3 failures in the 4.1 CI results, but all of them are present without this patch. Two are already tracked (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17298&quot; title=&quot;Improve accuracy of memtable heap usage tracking&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-17298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19702&quot; title=&quot;Test failure: largecolumn_test.TestLargeColumn&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-19702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), but I couldn&apos;t find an open JIRA for the &lt;tt&gt;ReadRepairTest&lt;/tt&gt; dtest failure.&lt;br/&gt;
The jvm17 dtest timeouts on trunk are most likely down to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19239&quot; title=&quot;jvm-dtests crash on java 17&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-19239&quot;&gt;CASSANDRA-19239&lt;/a&gt;, for which a fix is coming soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17863400" author="krummas" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2024 19:04:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17864544" author="beobal" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2024 08:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to 4.1 and merged to 5.0 &amp;amp; trunk, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
